10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>=C2=A0Programming note:</strong> <em>M=
oney Stuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p><h2 style=3D"font-=
weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-=
serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 30px; margin-bot=
tom: 0;">ESL ESG</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMjAvaG9tZXRvd24taW50ZXJuYXRpb25h=
bC1uZXctamVyc2V5LWRlbGktaXMtYWN0dWFsbHktd29ydGgtMi1iaWxsaW9u/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB440983fa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> wrote the other day</a> about how JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. go=
t in some hot water for agreeing to finance the European Super League, the =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23616625.292368/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmJjLmNvbS9zcG9ydC9mb290YmFsbC81Njg0MjQ0Mg/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB28991c88" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">now apparently dead</a> proposal to start a lucrative new league for=
 the biggest European soccer clubs. As the financier of this plan, JPMorgan=
 came in for a lot of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMS8wNC8xOS9idXNpbmV=
zcy9qcG1vcmdhbi1ldXJvcGVhbi1zdXBlci1sZWFndWUuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB6dbc6ef1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">abuse on Twitter</a> from European soccer fans. =E2=80=9CAccount is now c=
losed and this =C2=A332.25 is going elsewhere,=E2=80=9D tweeted one former =
Chase customer.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I thought this was funny, a=
nd I drew what I thought was a somewhat overwrought and tongue-in-cheek=C2=
=A0comparison between the Super League and other sorts of social responsibi=
lity decisions that banks make. My point, I suppose, was that =E2=80=9Cis t=
his bad for sports?=E2=80=9D is not really on the list of social responsibi=
lity and=C2=A0sustainability questions that banks generally ask when they c=
onsider new business. =E2=80=9CIs it bad for the environment,=E2=80=9D sure=
, =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2361662=
5.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMD=
QtMDcvYmxhY2tyb2NrLWJvcnJvd3MtYWdhaW5zdC1kaXZlcnNpdHk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB312ba74a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">is it=C2=A0good for diversity</a>,=E2=80=9D sure; there is a longish li=
st of topics that everyone understands are important for social responsibil=
ity, and new topics periodically get added to that list through various for=
ms of activism. But =E2=80=9Cis it good for soccer fans=E2=80=9D seemed, to=
 me, to be rather a different sort of topic, one that would be a little sil=
ly to add to the list.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nope, totally wrong,=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23616625.292368/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZ3VhcmRpYW4uY29tL2J1c2luZXNzLzIwMjEvYXByLzIxL2pwLW1vcmdh=
bi1jaGFzZS1nZXRzLXN1c3RhaW5hYmlsaXR5LWRvd25ncmFkZS1zdGFuZGFyZC1ldGhpY3MtYWZ=
0ZXItZnVuZGluZy1mYWlsZWQtc3VwZXItbGVhZ3Vl/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0f4a7aa3=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">it=E2=80=
=99s life-and-death stuff</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
A sustainability rating agency has downgraded JP Morgan Chase after the US =
bank was revealed to be funding the failed European Super League (ESL) brea=
kaway attempt.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Standard Ethics, which grade=
s corporations on their sustainability and is modelled on credit-ratings ag=
encies, criticised the clubs as well as the bank.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">=E2=80=9CStandard Ethics judges both the orientations shown by the f=
ootball clubs involved in the project and those of the US bank to be contra=
ry to sustainability best practices, which are defined by the agency accord=
ing to UN, OECD and European Union guidelines, and take into account the in=
terests of the stakeholders,=E2=80=9D it said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">It downgraded JP Morgan from an =E2=80=9Cadequate=E2=80=9D rating to =
=E2=80=9Cnon-compliant=E2=80=9D in light of the ESL. Standard Ethics charge=
s a fee to some companies to rate them based on environmental, social and g=
overnance performance, although JP Morgan=E2=80=99s rating was unsolicited.=
</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Every public-company chief ex=
ecutive officer <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23=
616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jAtMDEtMTcvc3Rha2Vob2xkZXJzLWdldC1hLWNvbW1pdHRlZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
bf1a134e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 loves to talk about</a> =E2=80=9Ctaking into account the interests of stak=
eholders,=E2=80=9D not least JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon. In 2019, the Busines=
s Roundtable, a group of public-company CEOs=C2=A0led by Dimon, concluded t=
hat =E2=80=9Cthe purpose of a corporation=E2=80=9D had changed and now it h=
ad to take into account =E2=80=9Call stakeholders.=E2=80=9D When I <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDgtMTkvbWF4aW1pemUt=
c2hhcmVob2xkZXItdmFsdWUtdG9wLWNlb3MtbWlnaHQtYmUtb3B0aW5nLW91dA/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cB29826972" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">made fun of the Business Roundtable statement</a>, I put a pic=
ture of Dimon at the top of my column. He=E2=80=99s a stakeholdery guy. It=
=E2=80=99s just that it apparently never occurred to him that sports fans a=
re stakeholders in the relevant sense.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Or here is =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjEtMDQtMjEvanBtb3JnYW4tZ2V0cy1jYXVnaHQtdXAtaW4tZXVyb3BlLXMtYmlnLXNvY2Nlci=
1sZWFndWUtYmx1bmRlcg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc90246f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">JPMorgan Gets Caught Up in Eu=
rope=E2=80=99s Big Soccer League Blunder</a>,=E2=80=9D from Bloomberg News:=
</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The size of the proposed finan=
cing meant the bank stood to receive millions of dollars in fees. Instead, =
the project appears doomed after most of the teams pulled out with fans, pl=
ayers and politicians decrying the plan. JPMorgan is now left to assess the=
 fallout from a proposal that appears to have underestimated the potential =
backlash from upending a sport with deep traditions and local roots.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt didn=E2=80=99t seem co-ordinated and =
almost didn=E2=80=99t seem thought through,=E2=80=9D said Steve Greenfield,=
 a professor of sports law at the University of Westminster. =E2=80=9CIt wa=
s business-based and lost sight of the sporting connotations.=E2=80=9D</p><=
/blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes! Right! Look: I am sure that a=
t least a few members of the JPMorgan deal team, or of the committees that =
approved the transaction, were European soccer fans. Like <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmx=
vb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMjIvd2h5LWV1cm9wZS1zLXN1cGVyLW=
xlYWd1ZS1pbXBsb2RlZC1vd25lcnMtZGlkbi10LWFjY291bnQtZm9yLWZhbnMtcGFzc2lvbg/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB097006de" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">most=C2=A0soccer fans</a>, I would guess, they proba=
bly believe in the importance of the pyramidal structure of club competitio=
ns; they think that the rigors and uncertainty of qualification for the Cha=
mpions League, and of promotion and relegation in domestic leagues, make fo=
r better games and a more interesting and meaningful sport. Probably some o=
f them worked diligently on this financing, and then went home to complain =
to their spouses that they were ruining the game of soccer. Probably some o=
f them made those complaints to each other, at the office, while working on=
 the financing.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But they put those personal=
 feelings aside because they work at a bank, and their job is to do big dea=
ls and earn big fees. They were =E2=80=9Cbusiness-based and lost sight of t=
he sporting connotations=E2=80=9D because they assumed that their job, at w=
ork, was to do business, and that the sporting connotations were a set of p=
ersonal aesthetic preferences that had no legitimate place at their work. I=
f your boss called you in=C2=A0and said =E2=80=9Cwe need you to work on thi=
s European Super League financing=E2=80=9D and you replied =E2=80=9CI=C2=A0=
can=E2=80=99t do that, I=E2=80=99m a Leicester fan,=E2=80=9D you would be =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0fired? Like that is just not a thing you can say! You can=E2=
=80=99t be like =E2=80=9CI am sorry but the sporting connotations just take=
 precedence over the business, for me.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Or, I mean, that=E2=80=99s how I and probably every single investment =
banker understood the situation as of last week. Right now, being bad for s=
ports seems to be going badly for JPMorgan, and for all I know now there=C2=
=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>a norm of social responsibility that your deals can=E2=
=80=99t make sports less sporting. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m sorry boss but I th=
ink this deal would be bad for the game of soccer=E2=80=9D is now a totally=
 reasonable thing for an investment banker to say, something really that a =
banker would be=C2=A0<em>obligated=C2=A0</em>to say, and to escalate to the=
 highest levels. Banks have a responsibility to the game of soccer, it turn=
s out.</p><h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&qu=
ot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; =
margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 0;">Archegos</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">The interesting thing about <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMDUvYmlsbC1od2FuZy1zLWFyY2hlZ29zLXN3YXAtYWZ0ZXJtYXRo=
LWlzLWF3a3dhcmQtZm9yLWJhbmtz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9194bca1" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Archegos Capital Man=
agement</a> is that it made very levered bets on a handful of stocks, and t=
hen those stocks went up a whole lot over a fairly short period of time. Th=
en they went down a whole lot, sure, wiping out Archegos and causing billio=
ns of dollars of losses for some of the banks that financed Archegos=E2=80=
=99s positions. But first they went up.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">One reason this matters is that, when Archegos first put on these positi=
ons, they were relatively small. Then they became big, by virtue of going u=
p. Archegos made very levered bets, and the bets kept winning, and Archegos=
 kept plowing its winnings into bigger levered bets. By the time it blew up=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0or by, like, a few days before it blew up =E2=80=94=C2=A0Ar=
chegos was a very large client of the banks who were financing its position=
s. But when it=C2=A0<em>started</em>, it wasn=E2=80=99t. I mean, it started=
 as a family office in 2013 with $200 million of assets, which is a small c=
lient as investment banks go, though one with a notable pedigree. (It=E2=80=
=99s the family office of Bill Hwang, who used to run Tiger Asia, an import=
ant =E2=80=9CTiger Cub=E2=80=9D hedge fund.) It grew over time into a bigge=
r and more=C2=A0important client. But its transformation into a <em>$20</em=
> <em>billion</em> fund with something like <em>$100 billion </em>of gross =
notional exposure happened within <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMDIvZ29kLWFuZC1tYW4tY29sbGlkZS1pbi1iaWxsLWh3YW5nLXMtZH=
VlbGluZy1saXZlcy1vbi13YWxsLXN0cmVldA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB70445c8d" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the last yea=
r or two</a>, through a series of large and rapidly successful bets.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So on the one hand there are stories about, for i=
nstance, Goldman Sachs Group Inc. salespeople <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/23616625.292368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDMtMjgvZ29sZG1hbi11LXR1cm4tb24taHdhbmctcHV0LW=
JhbmstYXQtbmV4dXMtb2YtbWFyZ2luLWNhbGwtbWF5aGVt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB95e=
43e84" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> th=
irstily pursuing Archegos</a> because they knew it was an active=C2=A0and l=
ucrative client for other banks. But on the other hand it is just about ima=
ginable that, for some of its banks, Archegos was kind of an out-of-the-way=
=C2=A0second-tier relationship, a client that nobody had heard of and that =
originally arrived as a mid-tier account. And some midlevel salesperson got=
 the account, and sold Archegos some swaps, and thought =E2=80=9Cwell that=
=E2=80=99s a nice little piece of business.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0And then the swap=
s kept going up and the notional kept ballooning, and the salesperson and t=
he trader kept looking at their reports and thinking =E2=80=9Chmm this is a=
 really big exposure, should we ... tell someone?=E2=80=9D[1] You don=E2=80=
=99t=C2=A0<em>have=C2=A0</em>to tell anyone, really; it=E2=80=99s all in th=
e reports, in the risk-management systems. (You hope!)=C2=A0What would you =
say? =E2=80=9CHey boss, just want to make sure you noticed that my Archegos=
